-- Silver Declines as Much as 0.5%, Reversing Advance to Highest Since 2008
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2010-09-23T04:38:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/silver-declines-as-much-as-0-5-reversing-advance-to-highest-since-2008.html
Silver for immediate delivery
declined as much as 0.5 percent to $21.0475 an ounce, reversing
an earlier gain that had taken the metal to the highest price
since March 2008. Silver traded at $21.0675 an ounce at 12:36
p.m. in Singapore.  To contact the reporter on this story:
